\s1 A man couldn’t walk, but Peter got Jesus to make him better
\p 
\v 1-3 There was a man that couldn’t walk. He was crippled all his life. Every day, somebody brought him to sit near one of the gates at God’s ceremony house. Everyone called that gate \em the beautiful gate\em*. As people went in through that gate, the crippled man asked them for money.
\p One day, at 3 o’clock in the afternoon, Peter and John went to pray at God’s ceremony house. They were going in through that Beautiful Gate, and that crippled man saw them and asked them for money.
