\s1 The big boss soldier took Paul to the Jewish Leaders Council
\p 
\v 30 \w The|strong="G2532"\w* big boss \w over|strong="G1519"\w* \w the|strong="G2532"\w* soldiers \w still|strong="G2476"\w* \w wanted|strong="G1014"\w* \w to|strong="G1519"\w* \w know|strong="G1097"\w* \w why|strong="G5101"\w* \w the|strong="G2532"\w* \w Jewish|strong="G2453"\w* leaders \w were|strong="G3588"\w* blaming \w Paul|strong="G3972"\w*, \w so|strong="G2532"\w* \w the|strong="G2532"\w* \w next|strong="G1887"\w* \w day|strong="G1887"\w* \w he|strong="G2532"\w* talked \w to|strong="G1519"\w* \w the|strong="G2532"\w* bosses \w of|strong="G5259"\w* \w the|strong="G2532"\w* \w Jewish|strong="G2453"\w* ceremonies, \w and|strong="G2532"\w* \w to|strong="G1519"\w* \w the|strong="G2532"\w* \w other|strong="G1161"\w* \w Jewish|strong="G2453"\w* Leaders \w Council|strong="G4892"\w* \w men|strong="G3956"\w*. \w He|strong="G2532"\w* told \w them|strong="G3588"\w* \w to|strong="G1519"\w* \w have|strong="G2532"\w* \w a|strong="G2532"\w* meeting. \w Then|strong="G2532"\w* \w he|strong="G2532"\w* \w took|strong="G2532"\w* \w Paul|strong="G3972"\w* \w to|strong="G1519"\w* \w that|strong="G3588"\w* meeting, \w and|strong="G2532"\w* \w he|strong="G2532"\w* \w took|strong="G2532"\w* \w off|strong="G3089"\w* \w his|strong="G1438"\w* chains, \w and|strong="G2532"\w* \w he|strong="G2532"\w* told \w Paul|strong="G3972"\w* \w to|strong="G1519"\w* \w stand|strong="G2476"\w* \w up|strong="G1519"\w* \w in|strong="G1519"\w* front \w of|strong="G5259"\w* \w them|strong="G3588"\w*, \w to|strong="G1519"\w* listen \w to|strong="G1519"\w* \w what|strong="G5101"\w* \w they|strong="G2532"\w* \w say|strong="G3956"\w*, \w and|strong="G2532"\w* \w to|strong="G1519"\w* tell \w his|strong="G1438"\w* story \w to|strong="G1519"\w* answer \w them|strong="G3588"\w*.
\c 23
\s1 A Jewish boss got angry with Paul
\p 
\v 1-2 One of the men at the Jewish Leaders Council meeting was the big boss of the Jewish ceremonies. His name was Ananias. Paul stood up in front of Ananias and all the men at the Jewish Leaders Council meeting, and he looked straight at them, and said, “My brothers, I have respected our God all my life, and I have always done whatever I reckoned was right.”
\p As soon as Paul said that, Ananias told the men that were near Paul to hit him on the mouth.
\p 
\v 3 \w Then|strong="G2532"\w* \w Paul|strong="G3972"\w* \w said|strong="G3004"\w* \w to|strong="G4314"\w* Ananias, “\w God|strong="G2316"\w* \w will|strong="G2316"\w* punish \w you|strong="G4771"\w* \w for|strong="G4314"\w* \w that|strong="G3588"\w*. \w You|strong="G4771"\w* reckon \w that|strong="G3588"\w* \w you|strong="G4771"\w* \w are|strong="G3588"\w* \w a|strong="G2532"\w* \w good|strong="G3588"\w* \w man|strong="G2316"\w*, \w but|strong="G2532"\w* \w you|strong="G4771"\w* \w are|strong="G3588"\w* \w not|strong="G2532"\w* \w a|strong="G2532"\w* \w good|strong="G3588"\w* \w man|strong="G2316"\w*. \w You|strong="G4771"\w* \w sit|strong="G2521"\w* \w there|strong="G2532"\w* \w to|strong="G4314"\w* \w judge|strong="G2919"\w* \w me|strong="G1473"\w* \w using|strong="G3004"\w* \w our|strong="G2316"\w* \w law|strong="G3551"\w*, \w but|strong="G2532"\w* \w you|strong="G4771"\w* don’\w t|strong="G3588"\w* follow \w that|strong="G3588"\w* \w law|strong="G3551"\w* \w yourself|strong="G4771"\w*. Nobody showed \w you|strong="G4771"\w* \w that|strong="G3588"\w* \w I|strong="G1473"\w* \w did|strong="G2532"\w* anything wrong, \w but|strong="G2532"\w* \w you|strong="G4771"\w* \w told|strong="G3004"\w* \w these|strong="G3588"\w* \w men|strong="G3588"\w* \w to|strong="G4314"\w* hit \w me|strong="G1473"\w*.”\x * \xo 23:3 \xt Matthew 23:27-28\x*
\p 
\v 4 \w The|strong="G1161"\w* \w men|strong="G3588"\w* \w that|strong="G3588"\w* \w were|strong="G3588"\w* \w standing|strong="G3936"\w* near \w Paul|strong="G3588"\w* \w said|strong="G3004"\w*, “\w You|strong="G3004"\w* \w are|strong="G3588"\w* \w saying|strong="G3004"\w* something bad \w to|strong="G3004"\w* \w God|strong="G2316"\w*’s \w man|strong="G2316"\w*, \w the|strong="G1161"\w* big boss \w of|strong="G2316"\w* \w our|strong="G2316"\w* Jewish ceremonies. \w You|strong="G3004"\w* \w can|strong="G3004"\w*’\w t|strong="G3588"\w* \w do|strong="G3004"\w* \w that|strong="G3588"\w*.”
\p 
\v 5 \w Paul|strong="G3972"\w* \w said|strong="G3004"\w*, “\w I|strong="G1063"\w*’m sorry, friends. \w I|strong="G1063"\w* didn’\w t|strong="G3588"\w* \w know|strong="G1492"\w* \w that|strong="G3754"\w* \w he|strong="G3754"\w* \w is|strong="G1510"\w* \w the|strong="G3588"\w* big boss \w of|strong="G2992"\w* \w our|strong="G1510"\w* Jewish ceremonies. \w I|strong="G1063"\w* \w know|strong="G1492"\w* \w that|strong="G3754"\w* Moses \w wrote|strong="G1125"\w* \w in|strong="G3004"\w* \w our|strong="G1510"\w* Jewish law, ‘Don’\w t|strong="G3588"\w* \w say|strong="G3004"\w* bad \w things|strong="G3588"\w* \w about|strong="G3754"\w* \w your|strong="G3588"\w* \w people|strong="G2992"\w*’s big boss.’”\x * \xo 23:5 \xt Exodus 22:28\x*
\s1 The soldiers took Paul away from the Jewish Leaders Council
\p 
\v 6-8 Some of the Jewish Leaders Council were men that belonged to the Sadducee mob, and others belonged to the Pharisee mob. The Sadducee mob believed that after people die, they will never become alive again. And they believed that there are no spirits, not even God’s angel messengers. But the Pharisee mob believed that all of those things are true, and they were strong for the Jewish law. Paul worked out that some of those council men were from the Sadducee mob, and some of them were from the Pharisee mob, so he shouted out loud to them. He said, “My friends, I’m a Pharisee man, like my father was. I believe that after people die, one day God will make them alive again. That’s the reason why I’m here in this court.”\x * \xo 23:6-8 \xt Matthew 22:23; Mark 12:18; Luke 20:27; Acts 26:5; Philippians 3:5\x*
\p As soon as Paul said that, the Pharisee mob and Sadducee mob started to argue with each other.
\v 9 \w The|strong="G1722"\w* council \w split|strong="G1096"\w* \w up|strong="G2532"\w* \w into|strong="G1722"\w* 2 mobs \w and|strong="G2532"\w* \w started|strong="G1096"\w* \w shouting|strong="G3004"\w* \w at|strong="G1722"\w* each \w other|strong="G1161"\w*. \w Some|strong="G5100"\w* \w of|strong="G4151"\w* \w the|strong="G1722"\w* teachers \w of|strong="G4151"\w* \w the|strong="G1722"\w* Jewish law \w were|strong="G3588"\w* \w from|strong="G2532"\w* \w the|strong="G1722"\w* \w Pharisee|strong="G5330"\w* mob. \w They|strong="G2532"\w* \w stood|strong="G3588"\w* \w up|strong="G2532"\w* \w and|strong="G2532"\w* \w said|strong="G3004"\w*, “\w We|strong="G2532"\w* reckon \w this|strong="G3778"\w* \w man|strong="G5100"\w* hasn’\w t|strong="G3588"\w* \w done|strong="G1096"\w* \w anything|strong="G5100"\w* \w wrong|strong="G2556"\w*. Maybe \w an|strong="G2532"\w* angel \w or|strong="G2228"\w* \w some|strong="G5100"\w* \w other|strong="G1161"\w* \w spirit|strong="G4151"\w* \w talked|strong="G2980"\w* \w to|strong="G2532"\w* \w him|strong="G3588"\w*. \w That|strong="G3588"\w*’s \w all|strong="G2532"\w* right.”
\p 
\v 10 \w Then|strong="G1161"\w* \w those|strong="G3588"\w* 2 mobs argued \w with|strong="G1537"\w* \w each|strong="G1519"\w* \w other|strong="G1161"\w* \w and|strong="G1161"\w* \w got|strong="G2597"\w* really wild, \w and|strong="G1161"\w* \w the|strong="G1519"\w* big boss soldier thought, “\w They|strong="G1161"\w* \w are|strong="G3588"\w* \w going|strong="G2597"\w* \w to|strong="G1519"\w* tear \w Paul|strong="G3972"\w* \w to|strong="G1519"\w* bits.” \w So|strong="G1161"\w* \w he|strong="G1161"\w* told \w his|strong="G1519"\w* \w soldiers|strong="G4753"\w*, “\w Go|strong="G2597"\w* \w and|strong="G1161"\w* \w save|strong="G3361"\w* \w Paul|strong="G3972"\w* \w from|strong="G1537"\w* \w those|strong="G3588"\w* council \w men|strong="G3588"\w*, \w and|strong="G1161"\w* \w take|strong="G1096"\w* \w him|strong="G3588"\w* \w back|strong="G1519"\w* \w to|strong="G1519"\w* \w your|strong="G5259"\w* big house.” \w So|strong="G1161"\w* \w the|strong="G1519"\w* \w soldiers|strong="G4753"\w* \w did|strong="G1096"\w* \w that|strong="G3588"\w*.
\s1 Jesus told Paul that he will go to Rome
\p 
