\v 2-3 “Big Boss Agrippa, I reckon I’m lucky. You know all about the culture of us Jews, and you know the things we argue about, and today you are hearing me talk. I reckon you will understand me. You see, the Jewish leaders are blaming me for a lot of things. So I ask you, please wait and listen to me now.” \fig Paul told Big Boss Agrippa why he was not guilty|src="CN02035b.tif" size="col" copy="1996 David C. Cook" ref="26:2-3"\fig*
